quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  50,31,"And Paradise will be brought near to the righteous, not far,"
  50,32,"[It will be said], "
  50,33,"Who feared the Most Merciful in the unseen and came with a heart returning [in repentance]."
  51,25,"When they entered upon him and said, "
  51,26,"Then he went to his family and came with a fat [roasted] calf."
  51,27,"And placed it near them; he said, "
  52,16,"[Enter to] burn therein; then be patient or impatient - it is all the same for you. You are only being recompensed [for] what you used to do."
  52,17,"Indeed, the righteous will be in gardens and pleasure,"
  52,18,"Enjoying what their Lord has given them, and their Lord protected them from the punishment of Hellfire."
  53,10,"And he revealed to His Servant{1} what he revealed [i.e., conveyed].",1:[i.e., to the Servant of Allāh, Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ).]
  53,11,"The heart{1} did not lie [about] what it saw.",1:[i.e., mind or perception (of the Prophet [ﷺ]).]
  53,12,"So will you dispute with him over what he saw?"
  54,1,"The Hour has come near, and the moon has split [in two].{1}",1:[This was a sign given by Allāh to Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ) when the Quraysh challenged him to show them a miracle.]
  54,2,"And if they see a sign [i.e., miracle], they turn away and say, ",1:[Or "Continuing magic."]
  54,3,"And they denied and followed their inclinations. But for every matter is a [time of] settlement."